  "prompt": "How is the movie \"Happy New Year\"?",
  "response": "\"Happy New Year\" is a 2014 Indian Hindi-language heist comedy-drama film directed by Farah Khan and produced by Gauri Khan under the banner of Red Chillies Entertainment. The film stars an ensemble cast including Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone, Abhishek Bachchan, and others.\n\nHere are some key points about the movie:\n\n1. **Plot**: The film follows a group of misfits who come together to plan a heist at the world dancing competition in order to seek revenge and clear their names.\n\n2. **Performances**: Shah Rukh Khan's performance, particularly his comic timing, was widely appreciated. Deepika Padukone's dance sequences also received praise.\n\n3. **Music and Dance**: The movie is known for its vibrant music and elaborate dance numbers, choreographed by notable choreographers like Farah Khan and Vaibhavi Merchant.\n\n4. **Critical Reception**: The film received mixed reviews from critics. Some appreciated the entertainment value, dance sequences, and performances, while others criticized the length and pacing of the film.\n\n5. **Box Office**: \"Happy New Year\" was a commercial success, becoming one of the highest-grossing Bollywood films of 2014.\n\nIf you enjoy Bollywood movies with a mix of comedy, drama, and dance, you might find \"Happy New Year\" entertaining. However, if you prefer more tightly scripted films, you might want to consider the mixed critical reception.",
